pdc_describe.title: For all data migration specs, check in Datacite XML fixtures and make sure the output is what we expect
changed vpill code in migration specs to Additional Metadata and/or Curator Controlled
New logger noise during test runs

comments.body:
- All the messages are the same: Pretty sure IDs are not being minted.
- Checking out earlier versions, I believe this was introduced by #907.
- Commenting out `state { "draft" }` [here](https://github.com/pulibrary/pdc_describe/pull/907/files#diff-aedd23a43d0cc72de8046469563e20ce15ffada49a80184ff8637b80bccea99a) seems to eliminate the excess logging, though it introduces two test failures:
```
rspec ./spec/system/work_edit_spec.rb:157 # Creating and updating works change log displays changes
rspec ./spec/system/work_edit_spec.rb:131 # Creating and updating works when editing funding information allows the user to edit funding information
```
- At least one test is failing because after the form POST, it is being 302 redirected to the home page: It looks like an error should be rendered, but I don't see anything on the screen.
```ruby
    elsif !@work.editable_in_current_state?(current_user)
      redirect_to root_path, notice: I18n.t("works.approved.uneditable")
```
- I tried adding `work.state = "draft"` to just this test. No change.
- Are flash messages actually being displayed on the homepage? In this case that doesn't seem to be the case.

princeton_ansible.title: [lib-jobs] peoplesoft mount doesn't always mount when required

comments.body: It's possible that the `ansible.posix.mount` module reads the `fstab` - I believe that running `umount` only removes the mount, without updating `fstab`. If that's true, then on the second run, the `mount.info` variable would not have reported changed.
